        <p>asphalt blues**Bruce Mathers letter on July 2 article on Route 66n</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Route 66 is the cold-water flat of American roadways. It's like taking a trip to the old neighborhood with your children or grandchildren to show them where you grew up and making sure the doors and windows are locked while you drive through.</p>
        <p>Bruce Mathers  Woodbury, Conn.</p>
      </block>
